Income Tax Act 1947 >> PART 20B INTERNATIONAL AGREEMENTS TOIMPROVE TAX COMPLIANCE >> 105P. Regulations to implement international tax compliance agreements, etc.: (1)The Minister may make regulations for, or in connection with, giving effect to or enabling effect to be given to—
(a) an international tax compliance agreement; or
